Wash and dry all produce. Preheat the #oven{} to 350 degrees. Cut the @demi-baguette{1} into 1-inch cubes. Halve the @grape tomatoes{4%oz}. Tear the @baby gem lettuce{1} into bite-sized pieces. Mince or grate the @garlic{2%cloves}. Thinly slice the @basil{1/2%oz} leaves. Zest, then halve the @lemon{1}. Cut the @fresh mozzarella{4%oz} into ½-inch cubes.

Toss the bread cubes on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @olive oil{} and a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Bake for about ~{8%minutes}, tossing halfway through cooking, until crispy.

In a #medium bowl{}, toss together the @shrimp{10%oz}, lemon zest, garlic, @chili powder{1%tsp}, a drizzle of oil, and a pinch of salt and pepper.

Cook the shrimp: Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add the shrimp to the pan and cook, tossing for ~{3-4%minutes}, until opaque.

In a #large bowl{}, toss together the shrimp, lettuce, tomatoes, mozzarella, bread cubes, a large drizzle of @olive oil{}, and a squeeze of lemon. Season with salt and pepper.

Plate and serve: Serve the citrusy shrimp panzanella divided between plates and sprinkled with basil and dig in!